	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">drk421 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is there a NES emulator that has a neato monitor/debugger like VICE (the Commodore 64 emu) ?</div>None that I know of, at least I haven't found any with symbolic debugging or a decent command prompt yet.
<br />Most emulators do offer a basic debugger though, so debugging is not completely hopeless, though I most of them seem better suited for tracing through existing ROMs than bugfixing.
<br />
<br />Sooner or later I'll try adding a decent debugger for development purposes to some popular emulator. After all, they're not *that* hard to write.
<br />
<br />The odd thing is that every other SMS emulator seems to offer such a debugger. So you'd think that someone would write one for the purpose of matching the SMS development scene if nothing else..

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


